  "prompt": "I'm sick of hearing about Trump, can I block these questions on my Quora feed?",
  "response": "Yes, you can manage your Quora feed to reduce content related to specific topics or users, including questions about Trump. Here are a few steps you can take:\n\n1. **Hide Questions**: When you see a question or answer about a topic you want to avoid, click on the three dots (\u22ee) next to the post and select \"Hide this question\" or \"Don't recommend this topic.\"\n\n2. **Unfollow Topics**: If you are following topics related to Trump or any political topics, you can unfollow them. Go to your profile, find the topics you follow, and select \"Unfollow\" for those you want to remove.\n\n3. **Adjust Interests**: Go to your settings and adjust your interests to focus on topics that interest you more, thereby reducing the likelihood of seeing unwanted content.\n\n4. **Provide Feedback**: Use the feedback options to let Quora know you don't want to see content related to certain topics.\n\nBy taking these steps, you can customize your Quora experience and minimize exposure to discussions about Trump or other subjects you wish to avoid.",
